1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,920
 to a happy Mother's Day.

2
00:00:01,920 --> 00:00:06,200
 Let me begin by a word of prayer.

3
00:00:06,200 --> 00:00:09,240
 I don't know what kind of spiritual condition

4
00:00:09,240 --> 00:00:11,560
 or what kind of emotional condition

5
00:00:11,560 --> 00:00:13,720
 you're coming into the presence of God,

6
00:00:13,720 --> 00:00:18,680
 but I want you to focus on God himself.

7
00:00:18,680 --> 00:00:21,880
 I want you to come in, not to see anyone else,

8
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:23,760
 but God himself, all right?

9
00:00:23,760 --> 00:00:25,760
 And know that God is for you.

10
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:27,760
 Know that God is present with you, all right?

11
00:00:27,760 --> 00:00:28,600
 Let's pray.

12
00:00:29,560 --> 00:00:31,080
 Father, we want to praise you.

13
00:00:31,080 --> 00:00:34,720
 We want to come before you and bow our knees.

14
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:39,160
 And I pray that you will be with us

15
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:41,840
 and help us to sense that you are with us,

16
00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:43,080
 you are present with us.

17
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:46,040
 I pray for each and every one of us.

18
00:00:46,040 --> 00:00:51,040
 Perhaps we have been fighting our battles

19
00:00:51,040 --> 00:00:54,960
 in the past week, our past few weeks.

20
00:00:54,960 --> 00:00:56,680
 We are fighting our worries.

21
00:00:56,680 --> 00:01:00,040
 We are dealing with our challenges.

22
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:03,600
 And sometimes our problems in our lives

23
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:05,440
 seem insurmountable.

24
00:01:05,440 --> 00:01:07,720
 It seems so big.

25
00:01:07,720 --> 00:01:12,360
 But we come before you, we know that you are bigger

26
00:01:12,360 --> 00:01:13,880
 and you're biggest.

27
00:01:13,880 --> 00:01:16,080
 You're bigger than anything else.

28
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:19,080
 And you got the whole wide world in your hand indeed.

29
00:01:19,080 --> 00:01:23,360
 And we pray that you will help us to put our trust in you

30
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:26,600
 and know that you are still in control.

31
00:01:27,240 --> 00:01:30,040
 You are still our king and our leader.

32
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:35,000
 Pray that you will forgive our sins,

33
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,760
 our shortcomings, our weaknesses.

34
00:01:37,760 --> 00:01:40,800
 And we come before you anew,

35
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:44,600
 knowing that your grace is always new every single morning.

36
00:01:44,600 --> 00:01:48,960
 So we pray that you will renew our commitment to you,

37
00:01:48,960 --> 00:01:50,320
 our trust in you.

38
00:01:50,320 --> 00:01:54,480
 No matter what barriers we are facing,

39
00:01:55,360 --> 00:01:58,280
 we know that you are bigger than all those challenges.

40
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:03,200
 And I pray that you're all powerful,

41
00:02:03,200 --> 00:02:07,520
 you're all knowing and your attributes will encourage us

42
00:02:07,520 --> 00:02:12,520
 to rely on you because you are worthy of our following.

43
00:02:12,520 --> 00:02:15,400
 So we pray that you will grant us grace

44
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:20,400
 to deal with our own depressed, unhappy,

45
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:24,800
 discomfort or discouragement.

46
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:27,800
 And I pray that you will encourage each and every one of us

47
00:02:27,800 --> 00:02:31,600
 in the spirit to continue to believe and trust in you.

48
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:34,520
 Knowing that as we follow you,

49
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:38,000
 we need to deny ourselves, bear our crosses,

50
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:44,000
 just like what your son Jesus has done for all of us.

51
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,880
 And I pray that we will be a community

52
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:47,800
 to encourage one another.

53
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:50,320
 As we have a Bible study together today,

54
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:55,280
 we pray that in the word we'll grow together.

55
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:57,080
 In the word we'll encourage one another

56
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,880
 to build up one another.

57
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:02,800
 Build up your church for your namesake, for your glory.

58
00:03:02,800 --> 00:03:07,920
 Also wanna pray for the mothers in our midst.

59
00:03:07,920 --> 00:03:11,480
 I pray that you will bless and grant grace

60
00:03:11,480 --> 00:03:13,080
 to every one of them.

61
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:16,760
 Thank you for our mothers.

62
00:03:16,760 --> 00:03:18,840
 Thank you for your divine appointment

63
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:22,080
 that we have only one mother

64
00:03:22,080 --> 00:03:25,160
 and the perfect mother for all of us.

65
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:28,400
 And I pray that you will bless every one of them.

66
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,800
 And thank you for using them, our mothers,

67
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:34,160
 to extend your love, to show your love.

68
00:03:34,160 --> 00:03:35,560
 Yes, we are all imperfect,

69
00:03:35,560 --> 00:03:40,560
 but you have shown us the perfect love on the cross.

70
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:43,840
 And thank you, Jesus, in Christ, we pray.

71
00:03:43,840 --> 00:03:48,600
 All right, today we're going to begin

72
00:03:48,600 --> 00:03:52,760
 our new mini-series on the Apostles' Creek.

73
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:57,120
 Now, James has told us we have our daily devotion

74
00:03:57,120 --> 00:03:59,680
 on the Apostles' Creek.

75
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:01,440
 So let's read this together.

76
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:02,560
 All right, let's read this together

77
00:04:02,560 --> 00:04:04,560
 and go through this together.

78
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:08,520
 We have the whole Apostles' Creek on the screen.

79
00:04:08,520 --> 00:04:13,520
 Now I want you to read this verse with the mentality,

80
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:19,160
 with the motive to evaluate what we really believe, okay?

81
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:24,800
 Sometimes when we go to church for a long time

82
00:04:24,800 --> 00:04:27,720
 and we've been to church for some time,

83
00:04:27,720 --> 00:04:30,480
 we have gotten what we truly believe

84
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,800
 or we have truncated our own belief.

85
00:04:32,800 --> 00:04:37,600
 We might have thought or we have truncated our belief

86
00:04:37,600 --> 00:04:41,880
 into just one or two things, and we make up our own idol.

87
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:46,600
 And in doing that, we are not believing the gospel anymore.

88
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,160
 And sometimes it is always good

89
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:52,040
 to reveal what we truly believe.

90
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:57,040
 And the Apostles' Creek is written for such a purpose

91
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:01,560
 so that we'll do a daily or regular check

92
00:05:01,560 --> 00:05:04,160
 of what you really believe, all right?

93
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:06,000
 Just like you go to the doctor.

94
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:09,040
 Now tomorrow, I'll go to the doctor for a regular checkup,

95
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:11,280
 okay, nothing wrong with me.

96
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:14,240
 You just have to do it once a year.

97
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:16,440
 But the doctor will tell me, okay,

98
00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:20,920
 your blood sugar level or your blood pressure

99
00:05:20,920 --> 00:05:22,320
 or anything wrong with me,

100
00:05:22,320 --> 00:05:24,560
 anything I need to pay attention to, right?

101
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:29,200
 So the Apostles' Creek is doing exactly

102
00:05:29,200 --> 00:05:34,960
 this sort of purpose, to check your belief, okay?

103
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:38,120
 The Apostles' Creek, let me read the left column.

104
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:41,760
 I believe in God, the Father Almighty,

105
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:43,680
 creator of heaven and earth.

106
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:47,080
 I believe in Jesus Christ, His only Son, our Lord.

107
00:05:47,080 --> 00:05:49,840
 He was conceived by the power of the Holy Spirit

108
00:05:49,840 --> 00:05:52,080
 and born of the Virgin Mary.

109
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:54,760
 He suffered under Pontius Pilate,

110
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:58,000
 was crucified, died, and was buried.

111
00:05:58,000 --> 00:05:59,960
 He descended to the dead.

112
00:05:59,960 --> 00:06:02,000
 On the third day, He rose again.

113
00:06:02,000 --> 00:06:03,600
 He ascended into heaven

114
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,440
 and is seated at the right hand of the Father.

115
00:06:06,440 --> 00:06:09,880
 He will come again to judge the living and the dead.

116
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:14,880
 I believe in the Holy Spirit, the Holy Universal Church,

117
00:06:14,880 --> 00:06:18,640
 the chameleon of saints, the forgiveness of sins,

118
00:06:18,640 --> 00:06:23,220
 the resurrection of the body, and life everlasting, amen.

119
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:26,120
 This is the Apostles' Creek.

120
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:28,800
 Now, it's a quick summary

121
00:06:28,800 --> 00:06:32,480
 to tell you what our basic belief is.

122
00:06:32,480 --> 00:06:34,560
 Of course, it's not just that,

123
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,680
 but it's good enough summary

124
00:06:36,680 --> 00:06:38,680
 to tell you what you truly believe,

125
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:42,040
 what are the central core beliefs, okay?

126
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:44,760
 Now, how many of you have been to Chicago for some time,

127
00:06:44,760 --> 00:06:46,520
 for at least one year?

128
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:47,340
 How many of you?

129
00:06:47,340 --> 00:06:49,880
 All right, no one is new to Chicago, right?

